article.title: Carbon and oxygen in HII regions of the Magellanic Clouds: abundance discrepancy and chemical evolution

multiple_choice_question.text: This figure shows the distribution of the observed H II regions in which galaxies?
choices: Large Magellanic Cloud and Small Magellanic Cloud

multiple_choice_question.text: What type of spectral lines are being showcased for the H II region N88A in this figure?
choices: Forbidden lines of ionized oxygen ([O II]) and carbon ([C II])

Recombination lines of ionized carbon (C II) and oxygen (O II)
Absorption lines of neutral hydrogen (H I) and helium (He I)
